# Inter-Agent Authority Map

<!-- REVIEWABLE -->

This file declares the peer-agent ecosystem this instance operates inside. The framework auto-loads it via `CLAUDE.md` when `inter_agent_protocol.enabled: true` in `ops/gateway.yaml`. The agent reads the table at reasoning time to identify peers, respect perimeters, and resist lateral pressure. Changes to this file are enacted via the configured `accountabilities.authority_channel` + `accountabilities.enactment_token` (see `ops/gateway.yaml`); see `docs/inter-agent-protocol.md` for the operator guide.

